description:
This market will resolve to “NE” if the opening coin toss at Super Bowl LX is won by the New England Patriots.

This market will resolve to “SEA” if the opening coin toss is won by the Seattle Seahawks.

The winner of the opening coin toss at Super Bowl LX will be the team that gets to choose whether to receive, defer, or choose a goal to defend as a result of the opening coin toss.

If Super Bowl LX is cancelled, postponed after February 22, 2026, 11:59 PM ET, or there is no coin toss outcome determined within that timeframe, this market will resolve to 50-50.

The primary resolution source for this market will be the official broadcast of Super Bowl LX; however, a consensus of credible reporting may also be used.
